Date of Birth: November 3, 1807<br/>
Birthplace: Pomfret, Vermont, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: February 15, 1835<br/>
Excommunicated: April 13, 1838<br/>
Rebaptized: 1846<br/>
Death: December 9, 1861<br/>
<br/>
Born Nov. 3, 1807, at Pomfret, Windsor Co., Vermont, to John Johnson and Elsa Jacobs. Ordained apostle Feb. 15, 1835, by Oliver Cowdery, David Whitmer, and Martin Harris, at Kirtland, Ohio, at age 27;
excommunicated April 13, 1838; rebaptized in 1846 at Nauvoo, Illinois; died Dec. 9, 1861, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 54.